## Early game

**Gulliver** on Phobos (Defense, Corpus Ship, levels 10-15) is one of the few
main-planet nodes with a decent Plastids drop chance for a fresh account —
Phobos is a signature Plastids planet, and this Defense is short enough to
repeat a few times in a session without much of a level requirement.

## Mid & late game

Plastids are notoriously low-yield no matter where you farm them, so the
endgame play is a dedicated squad run rather than solo resets. **Assur** on
Uranus (Dark Sector Survival, Infested Grineer Galleon, levels 25-35, Steel
Path) is the best of these: the Dark Sector resource bonus plus Steel Path
enemy density give a loot squad (Nekros, Hydroid) enough enemy throughput to
make a long rotation worthwhile.

